creator: Samuel Johnson; Stuart Johnson Reid
description:
LibriVox recording of Selected Essays of Samuel Johnson by Samuel Johnson; Stuart Johnson Reid.
Read in English by Barbara Baker; Bill Boerst; Availle; Pamela Nagami; Denise Nordell; Jesse Zuba; Roohi; Michele Fry; J. McDougall; Anders V Lankford; Philippa
This is a volume of selected essays by "the great master of reason" Samuel Johnson. The most famous exerpts from The Rambler, The Adventurer and The Idler are included, covering a vast range of topics. - Summary by Carolin
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
